Package: semFromKeys
Type: Package
Title: Run `lavaan` Models From Keys Lists
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Timothy F.", "Bainbridge",
      email = "tfbainbridge@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")
    )
  )
Description: Specifying lavaan models manually can be time consuming when
    multiple similar models are required. The semFromKeys package aims to
    streamline the process of running lavaan models by generating model code
    from simple keys lists instead of writing out model code manually.
    The package also optionally checks that identical models have not been run
    on the same data, which saves time when code needs to be run again.
    For structural models, functions use Burt's (1976)
    <doi:doi.org/10.1177/004912417600500101> procedure to control for
    interpretational confounding.
